8 // ----
9 // This file implements a pass to prepare loops for ppc preferred addressing ----
10 // modes, leveraging different instruction form. (eg: DS/DQ form, D/DS form with ----
11 // update) ----
12 // Additional PHIs are created for loop induction variables used by load/store ----
13 // instructions so that preferred addressing modes can be used. ----
14 // ----
15 // 1: DS/DQ form preparation, prepare the load/store instructions so that they ----
16 // can satisfy the DS/DQ form displacement requirements. ----
17 // Generically, this means transforming loops like this: ----
18 // for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) { ----
19 // unsigned long x1 = *(unsigned long *)(p + i + 5); ----
20 // unsigned long x2 = *(unsigned long *)(p + i + 9); ----
21 // } ----
22 // ----
23 // to look like this: ----
24 // ----
25 // unsigned NewP = p + 5; ----
26 // for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) { ----
27 // unsigned long x1 = *(unsigned long *)(i + NewP); ----
28 // unsigned long x2 = *(unsigned long *)(i + NewP + 4); ----
29 // } ----
30 // ----
31 // 2: D/DS form with update preparation, prepare the load/store instructions so ----
32 // that we can use update form to do pre-increment. ----
33 // Generically, this means transforming loops like this: ----
34 // for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) ----
35 // array[i] = c; ----
36 // ----
37 // to look like this: ----
38 // ----
39 // T *p = array[-1]; ----
40 // for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) ----
41 // *++p = c; ----
42 // ----
43 // 3: common multiple chains for the load/stores with same offsets in the loop, ----
44 // so that we can reuse the offsets and reduce the register pressure in the ----
45 // loop. This transformation can also increase the loop ILP as now each chain ----
46 // uses its own loop induction add/addi. But this will increase the number of ----
47 // add/addi in the loop. ----
48 // ----
49 // Generically, this means transforming loops like this: ----
50 // ----
51 // char *p; ----
52 // A1 = p + base1 ----
53 // A2 = p + base1 + offset ----
54 // B1 = p + base2 ----
55 // B2 = p + base2 + offset ----
56 // ----
57 // for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) ----
58 // unsigned long x1 = *(unsigned long *)(A1 + i); ----
59 // unsigned long x2 = *(unsigned long *)(A2 + i) ----
60 // unsigned long x3 = *(unsigned long *)(B1 + i); ----
61 // unsigned long x4 = *(unsigned long *)(B2 + i); ----
62 // } ----
63 // ----
64 // to look like this: ----
65 // ----
66 // A1_new = p + base1 // chain 1 ----
67 // B1_new = p + base2 // chain 2, now inside the loop, common offset is ----
68 // // reused. ----
69 // ----
70 // for (long long i = 0; i < n; i+=count) { ----
71 // unsigned long x1 = *(unsigned long *)(A1_new + i); ----
72 // unsigned long x2 = *(unsigned long *)((A1_new + i) + offset); ----
73 // unsigned long x3 = *(unsigned long *)(B1_new + i); ----
74 // unsigned long x4 = *(unsigned long *)((B1_new + i) + offset); ----
75 // } ----
76 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----

152 ----
153 // Commoning chain will reduce the register pressure, so we don't consider about ----
154 // the PHI nodes number. ----
155 // But commoning chain will increase the addi/add number in the loop and also ----
156 // increase loop ILP. Maximum chain number should be same with hardware ----
157 // IssueWidth, because we won't benefit from ILP if the parallel chains number ----
158 // is bigger than IssueWidth. We assume there are 2 chains in one bucket, so ----
159 // there would be 4 buckets at most on P9(IssueWidth is 8). ----
160 static cl::opt MaxVarsChainCommon( ----
161 "ppc-chaincommon-max-vars", cl::Hidden, cl::init(4), ----
162 cl::desc("Bucket number per loop for PPC loop chain common")); ----
163 ----
164 // If would not be profitable if the common base has only one load/store, ISEL ----
165 // should already be able to choose best load/store form based on offset for ----
166 // single load/store. Set minimal profitable value default to 2 and make it as ----
167 // an option. ----
168 static cl::opt DispFormPrepMinThreshold("ppc-dispprep-min-threshold", ----
169 cl::Hidden, cl::init(2), ----
170 cl::desc("Minimal common base load/store instructions triggering DS/DQ form " ----
171 "preparation")); ----

176 "commoning preparation. Must be not smaller than 4")); ----

196 Bucket(const SCEV *B, Instruction *I) 0

198 ChainSize = 0; 0
199 } 0
200 ----
201 // The base of the whole bucket. ----

203 ----

216 // "UpdateForm" is not a real PPC instruction form, it stands for dform ----
217 // load/store with update like ldu/stdu, or Prefetch intrinsic. ----
218 // For DS form instructions, their displacements must be multiple of 4. ----
219 // For DQ form instructions, their displacements must be multiple of 16. ----
220 enum PrepForm { UpdateForm = 1, DSForm = 4, DQForm = 16, ChainCommoning }; ----

356 static bool IsPtrInBounds(Value *BasePtr) { 0
357 Value *StrippedBasePtr = BasePtr; 0
358 while (BitCastInst *BC = dyn_cast(StrippedBasePtr)) 0
359 StrippedBasePtr = BC->getOperand(0); 0
360 if (GetElementPtrInst *GEP = dyn_cast(StrippedBasePtr)) 0
361 return GEP->isInBounds(); 0
362 ----
363 return false; 0
364 } ----

374 static Value *getPointerOperandAndType(Value *MemI, 0
375 Type **PtrElementType = nullptr) { ----
376 ----
377 Value *PtrValue = nullptr; 0
378 Type *PointerElementType = nullptr; 0
379 ----
380 if (LoadInst *LMemI = dyn_cast(MemI)) { 0
381 PtrValue = LMemI->getPointerOperand(); 0
382 PointerElementType = LMemI->getType(); 0
383 } else if (StoreInst *SMemI = dyn_cast(MemI)) { 0
384 PtrValue = SMemI->getPointerOperand(); 0
385 PointerElementType = SMemI->getValueOperand()->getType(); 0
386 } else if (IntrinsicInst *IMemI = dyn_cast(MemI)) { 0
387 PointerElementType = Type::getInt8Ty(MemI->getContext()); 0
388 if (IMemI->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::prefetch || 0
389 IMemI->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_lxvp) { 0
390 PtrValue = IMemI->getArgOperand(0); 0
391 } else if (IMemI->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::ppc_vsx_stxvp) { 0
392 PtrValue = IMemI->getArgOperand(1); 0
393 } ----
394 } ----
395 /*Get ElementType if PtrElementType is not null.*/ ----
396 if (PtrElementType) 0
397 *PtrElementType = PointerElementType; 0
398 ----
399 return PtrValue; 0
400 } ----

402 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::runOnFunction(Function &F) { 0
403 if (skipFunction(F)) 0
404 return false; 0
405 ----
406 LI = &getAnalysis().getLoopInfo(); 0
407 SE = &getAnalysis().getSE(); 0
408 auto *DTWP = getAnalysisIfAvailable(); 0
409 DT = DTWP ? &DTWP->getDomTree() : nullptr; 0
410 PreserveLCSSA = mustPreserveAnalysisID(LCSSAID); 0
411 ST = TM ? TM->getSubtargetImpl(F) : nullptr; 0
412 SuccPrepCount = 0; 0
413 ----
414 bool MadeChange = false; 0
415 ----
416 for (Loop *I : *LI) 0
417 for (Loop *L : depth_first(I)) 0
418 MadeChange |= runOnLoop(L); 0
419 ----
420 return MadeChange; 0
421 } ----
422 ----
423 // Finding the minimal(chain_number + reusable_offset_number) is a complicated ----
424 // algorithmic problem. ----
425 // For now, the algorithm used here is simply adjusted to handle the case for ----
426 // manually unrolling cases. ----
427 // FIXME: use a more powerful algorithm to find minimal sum of chain_number and ----
428 // reusable_offset_number for one base with multiple offsets. ----
429 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::prepareBasesForCommoningChains(Bucket &CBucket) { 0
430 // The minimal size for profitable chain commoning: ----
431 // A1 = base + offset1 ----
432 // A2 = base + offset2 (offset2 - offset1 = X) ----
433 // A3 = base + offset3 ----
434 // A4 = base + offset4 (offset4 - offset3 = X) ----
435 // ======> ----
436 // base1 = base + offset1 ----
437 // base2 = base + offset3 ----
438 // A1 = base1 ----
439 // A2 = base1 + X ----
440 // A3 = base2 ----
441 // A4 = base2 + X ----
442 // ----
443 // There is benefit because of reuse of offest 'X'. ----
444 ----
445 assert(ChainCommonPrepMinThreshold >= 4 && 0
446 "Thredhold can not be smaller than 4!\n"); ----
447 if (CBucket.Elements.size() < ChainCommonPrepMinThreshold) 0
448 return false; 0
449 ----
450 // We simply select the FirstOffset as the first reusable offset between each ----
451 // chain element 1 and element 0. ----
452 const SCEV *FirstOffset = CBucket.Elements[1].Offset; 0
453 ----
454 // Figure out how many times above FirstOffset is used in the chain. ----
455 // For a success commoning chain candidate, offset difference between each ----
456 // chain element 1 and element 0 must be also FirstOffset. ----
457 unsigned FirstOffsetReusedCount = 1; 0
458 ----
459 // Figure out how many times above FirstOffset is used in the first chain. ----
460 // Chain number is FirstOffsetReusedCount / FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain ----
461 unsigned FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain = 1; 0
462 ----
463 unsigned EleNum = CBucket.Elements.size(); 0
464 bool SawChainSeparater = false; 0
465 for (unsigned j = 2; j != EleNum; ++j) { 0
466 if (SE->getMinusSCEV(CBucket.Elements[j].Offset, 0
467 CBucket.Elements[j - 1].Offset) == FirstOffset) { 0
468 if (!SawChainSeparater) 0
469 FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain++; 0
470 FirstOffsetReusedCount++; 0
471 } else ----
472 // For now, if we meet any offset which is not FirstOffset, we assume we ----
473 // find a new Chain. ----
474 // This makes us miss some opportunities. ----
475 // For example, we can common: ----
476 // ----
477 // {OffsetA, Offset A, OffsetB, OffsetA, OffsetA, OffsetB} ----
478 // ----
479 // as two chains: ----
480 // {{OffsetA, Offset A, OffsetB}, {OffsetA, OffsetA, OffsetB}} ----
481 // FirstOffsetReusedCount = 4; FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain = 2 ----
482 // ----
483 // But we fail to common: ----
484 // ----
485 // {OffsetA, OffsetB, OffsetA, OffsetA, OffsetB, OffsetA} ----
486 // FirstOffsetReusedCount = 4; FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain = 1 ----
487 ----
488 SawChainSeparater = true; 0
489 } ----
490 ----
491 // FirstOffset is not reused, skip this bucket. ----
492 if (FirstOffsetReusedCount == 1) 0
493 return false; 0
494 ----
495 unsigned ChainNum = 0
496 FirstOffsetReusedCount / FirstOffsetReusedCountInFirstChain; ----
497 ----
498 // All elements are increased by FirstOffset. ----
499 // The number of chains should be sqrt(EleNum). ----
500 if (!SawChainSeparater) 0
501 ChainNum = (unsigned)sqrt((double)EleNum); 0
502 ----
503 CBucket.ChainSize = (unsigned)(EleNum / ChainNum); 0
504 ----
505 // If this is not a perfect chain(eg: not all elements can be put inside ----
506 // commoning chains.), skip now. ----
507 if (CBucket.ChainSize * ChainNum != EleNum) 0
508 return false; 0
509 ----
510 if (SawChainSeparater) { 0
511 // Check that the offset seqs are the same for all chains. ----
512 for (unsigned i = 1; i < CBucket.ChainSize; i++) 0
513 for (unsigned j = 1; j < ChainNum; j++) 0
514 if (CBucket.Elements[i].Offset != 0
515 SE->getMinusSCEV(CBucket.Elements[i + j * CBucket.ChainSize].Offset, 0
516 CBucket.Elements[j * CBucket.ChainSize].Offset)) 0
517 return false; 0
518 } ----
519 ----
520 for (unsigned i = 0; i < ChainNum; i++) 0
521 CBucket.ChainBases.push_back(CBucket.Elements[i * CBucket.ChainSize]); 0
522 ----
523 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Bucket has " << ChainNum << " chains.\n"); 0
524 ----
525 return true; 0
526 } ----
527 ----
528 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::chainCommoning(Loop *L, 0
529 SmallVector &Buckets) { ----
530 bool MadeChange = false; 0
531 ----
532 if (Buckets.empty()) 0
533 return MadeChange; 0
534 ----
535 SmallSet BBChanged; 0
536 ----
537 for (auto &Bucket : Buckets) { 0
538 if (prepareBasesForCommoningChains(Bucket)) 0
539 MadeChange |= rewriteLoadStoresForCommoningChains(L, Bucket, BBChanged); 0
540 } ----
541 ----
542 if (MadeChange) 0
543 for (auto *BB : BBChanged) 0
544 DeleteDeadPHIs(BB); 0
545 return MadeChange; 0
546 } 0
547 ----
548 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::rewriteLoadStoresForCommoningChains( 0
549 Loop *L, Bucket &Bucket, SmallSet &BBChanged) { ----
550 bool MadeChange = false; 0
551 ----
552 assert(Bucket.Elements.size() == 0
553 Bucket.ChainBases.size() * Bucket.ChainSize && ----
554 "invalid bucket for chain commoning!\n"); ----
555 SmallPtrSet DeletedPtrs; 0
556 ----
557 BasicBlock *Header = L->getHeader(); 0
558 BasicBlock *LoopPredecessor = L->getLoopPredecessor(); 0
559 ----
560 SCEVExpander SCEVE(*SE, Header->getModule()->getDataLayout(), 0
561 "loopprepare-chaincommon"); 0
562 ----
563 for (unsigned ChainIdx = 0; ChainIdx < Bucket.ChainBases.size(); ++ChainIdx) { 0
564 unsigned BaseElemIdx = Bucket.ChainSize * ChainIdx; 0
565 const SCEV *BaseSCEV = ----
566 ChainIdx ? SE->getAddExpr(Bucket.BaseSCEV, 0
567 Bucket.Elements[BaseElemIdx].Offset) 0
568 : Bucket.BaseSCEV; 0
569 const SCEVAddRecExpr *BasePtrSCEV = cast(BaseSCEV); 0
570 ----
571 // Make sure the base is able to expand. ----
572 if (!SCEVE.isSafeToExpand(BasePtrSCEV->getStart())) 0
573 return MadeChange; 0
574 ----
575 assert(BasePtrSCEV->isAffine() && 0
576 "Invalid SCEV type for the base ptr for a candidate chain!\n"); ----
577 ----
578 std::pair Base = rewriteForBase( 0
579 L, BasePtrSCEV, Bucket.Elements[BaseElemIdx].Instr, 0
580 false /* CanPreInc */, ChainCommoning, SCEVE, DeletedPtrs); ----
581 ----
582 if (!Base.first || !Base.second) 0
583 return MadeChange; 0
584 ----
585 // Keep track of the replacement pointer values we've inserted so that we ----
586 // don't generate more pointer values than necessary. ----
587 SmallPtrSet NewPtrs; 0
588 NewPtrs.insert(Base.first); 0
589 ----
590 for (unsigned Idx = BaseElemIdx + 1; Idx < BaseElemIdx + Bucket.ChainSize; 0
591 ++Idx) { ----
592 BucketElement &I = Bucket.Elements[Idx]; 0
593 Value *Ptr = getPointerOperandAndType(I.Instr); 0
594 assert(Ptr && "No pointer operand"); 0
595 if (NewPtrs.count(Ptr)) 0
596 continue; 0
597 ----
598 const SCEV *OffsetSCEV = ----
599 BaseElemIdx ? SE->getMinusSCEV(Bucket.Elements[Idx].Offset, 0
600 Bucket.Elements[BaseElemIdx].Offset) 0
601 : Bucket.Elements[Idx].Offset; 0
602 ----
603 // Make sure offset is able to expand. Only need to check one time as the ----
604 // offsets are reused between different chains. ----
605 if (!BaseElemIdx) 0
606 if (!SCEVE.isSafeToExpand(OffsetSCEV)) 0
607 return false; 0
608 ----
609 Value *OffsetValue = SCEVE.expandCodeFor( 0
610 OffsetSCEV, OffsetSCEV->getType(), LoopPredecessor->getTerminator()); ----
611 ----
612 Instruction *NewPtr = rewriteForBucketElement(Base, Bucket.Elements[Idx], 0
613 OffsetValue, DeletedPtrs); ----
614 ----
615 assert(NewPtr && "Wrong rewrite!\n"); 0
616 NewPtrs.insert(NewPtr); 0
617 } ----
618 ----
619 ++ChainCommoningRewritten; 0
620 } 0
621 ----
622 // Clear the rewriter cache, because values that are in the rewriter's cache ----
623 // can be deleted below, causing the AssertingVH in the cache to trigger. ----
624 SCEVE.clear(); 0
625 ----
626 for (auto *Ptr : DeletedPtrs) { 0
627 if (Instruction *IDel = dyn_cast(Ptr)) 0
628 BBChanged.insert(IDel->getParent()); 0
629 RecursivelyDeleteTriviallyDeadInstructions(Ptr); 0
630 } ----
631 ----
632 MadeChange = true; 0
633 return MadeChange; 0
634 } 0
635 ----
636 // Rewrite the new base according to BasePtrSCEV. ----
637 // bb.loop.preheader: ----
638 // %newstart = ... ----
639 // bb.loop.body: ----
640 // %phinode = phi [ %newstart, %bb.loop.preheader ], [ %add, %bb.loop.body ] ----
641 // ... ----
642 // %add = getelementptr %phinode, %inc ----
643 // ----
644 // First returned instruciton is %phinode (or a type cast to %phinode), caller ----
645 // needs this value to rewrite other load/stores in the same chain. ----
646 // Second returned instruction is %add, caller needs this value to rewrite other ----
647 // load/stores in the same chain. ----
648 std::pair ----
649 PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::rewriteForBase(Loop *L, const SCEVAddRecExpr *BasePtrSCEV, 0
650 Instruction *BaseMemI, bool CanPreInc, ----
651 PrepForm Form, SCEVExpander &SCEVE, ----
652 SmallPtrSet &DeletedPtrs) { ----
653 ----
654 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "PIP: Transforming: " << *BasePtrSCEV << "\n"); 0
655 ----
656 assert(BasePtrSCEV->getLoop() == L && "AddRec for the wrong loop?"); 0
657 ----
658 Value *BasePtr = getPointerOperandAndType(BaseMemI); 0
659 assert(BasePtr && "No pointer operand"); 0
660 ----
661 Type *I8Ty = Type::getInt8Ty(BaseMemI->getParent()->getContext()); 0
662 Type *I8PtrTy = ----
663 Type::getInt8PtrTy(BaseMemI->getParent()->getContext(), 0
664 BasePtr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()); ----
665 ----
666 bool IsConstantInc = false; 0
667 const SCEV *BasePtrIncSCEV = BasePtrSCEV->getStepRecurrence(*SE); 0
668 Value *IncNode = getNodeForInc(L, BaseMemI, BasePtrIncSCEV); 0
669 ----
670 const SCEVConstant *BasePtrIncConstantSCEV = ----
671 dyn_cast(BasePtrIncSCEV); 0
672 if (BasePtrIncConstantSCEV) 0
673 IsConstantInc = true; 0
674 ----
675 // No valid representation for the increment. ----
676 if (!IncNode) { 0
677 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Loop Increasement can not be represented!\n"); 0
678 return std::make_pair(nullptr, nullptr); 0
679 } ----
680 ----
681 if (Form == UpdateForm && !IsConstantInc && !EnableUpdateFormForNonConstInc) { 0
682 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
683 dbgs() ----
684 << "Update form prepare for non-const increment is not enabled!\n"); ----
685 return std::make_pair(nullptr, nullptr); 0
686 } ----
687 ----
688 const SCEV *BasePtrStartSCEV = nullptr; 0
689 if (CanPreInc) { 0
690 assert(SE->isLoopInvariant(BasePtrIncSCEV, L) && 0
691 "Increment is not loop invariant!\n"); ----
692 BasePtrStartSCEV = SE->getMinusSCEV(BasePtrSCEV->getStart(), 0
693 IsConstantInc ? BasePtrIncConstantSCEV ----
694 : BasePtrIncSCEV); ----
695 } else ----
696 BasePtrStartSCEV = BasePtrSCEV->getStart(); 0
697 ----
698 if (alreadyPrepared(L, BaseMemI, BasePtrStartSCEV, BasePtrIncSCEV, Form)) { 0
699 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Instruction form is already prepared!\n"); 0
700 return std::make_pair(nullptr, nullptr); 0
701 } ----
702 ----
703 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "PIP: New start is: " << *BasePtrStartSCEV << "\n"); 0
704 ----
705 BasicBlock *Header = L->getHeader(); 0
706 unsigned HeaderLoopPredCount = pred_size(Header); 0
707 BasicBlock *LoopPredecessor = L->getLoopPredecessor(); 0
708 ----
709 PHINode *NewPHI = PHINode::Create(I8PtrTy, HeaderLoopPredCount, 0
710 getInstrName(BaseMemI, PHINodeNameSuffix), 0
711 Header->getFirstNonPHI()); ----
712 ----
713 Value *BasePtrStart = SCEVE.expandCodeFor(BasePtrStartSCEV, I8PtrTy, 0
714 LoopPredecessor->getTerminator()); ----
715 ----
716 // Note that LoopPredecessor might occur in the predecessor list multiple ----
717 // times, and we need to add it the right number of times. ----
718 for (auto *PI : predecessors(Header)) { 0
719 if (PI != LoopPredecessor) 0
720 continue; 0
721 ----
722 NewPHI->addIncoming(BasePtrStart, LoopPredecessor); 0
723 } ----
724 ----
725 Instruction *PtrInc = nullptr; 0
726 Instruction *NewBasePtr = nullptr; 0
727 if (CanPreInc) { 0
728 Instruction *InsPoint = &*Header->getFirstInsertionPt(); 0
729 PtrInc = GetElementPtrInst::Create( 0
730 I8Ty, NewPHI, IncNode, getInstrName(BaseMemI, GEPNodeIncNameSuffix), 0
731 InsPoint); ----
732 cast(PtrInc)->setIsInBounds(IsPtrInBounds(BasePtr)); 0
733 for (auto *PI : predecessors(Header)) { 0
734 if (PI == LoopPredecessor) 0
735 continue; 0
736 ----
737 NewPHI->addIncoming(PtrInc, PI); 0
738 } ----
739 if (PtrInc->getType() != BasePtr->getType()) 0
740 NewBasePtr = 0
741 new BitCastInst(PtrInc, BasePtr->getType(), 0
742 getInstrName(PtrInc, CastNodeNameSuffix), InsPoint); 0
743 else ----
744 NewBasePtr = PtrInc; 0
745 } else { ----
746 // Note that LoopPredecessor might occur in the predecessor list multiple ----
747 // times, and we need to make sure no more incoming value for them in PHI. ----
748 for (auto *PI : predecessors(Header)) { 0
749 if (PI == LoopPredecessor) 0
750 continue; 0
751 ----
752 // For the latch predecessor, we need to insert a GEP just before the ----
753 // terminator to increase the address. ----
754 BasicBlock *BB = PI; 0
755 Instruction *InsPoint = BB->getTerminator(); 0
756 PtrInc = GetElementPtrInst::Create( 0
757 I8Ty, NewPHI, IncNode, getInstrName(BaseMemI, GEPNodeIncNameSuffix), 0
758 InsPoint); ----
759 cast(PtrInc)->setIsInBounds(IsPtrInBounds(BasePtr)); 0
760 ----
761 NewPHI->addIncoming(PtrInc, PI); 0
762 } ----
763 PtrInc = NewPHI; 0
764 if (NewPHI->getType() != BasePtr->getType()) 0
765 NewBasePtr = new BitCastInst(NewPHI, BasePtr->getType(), 0
766 getInstrName(NewPHI, CastNodeNameSuffix), 0
767 &*Header->getFirstInsertionPt()); 0
768 else ----
769 NewBasePtr = NewPHI; 0
770 } ----
771 ----
772 BasePtr->replaceAllUsesWith(NewBasePtr); 0
773 ----
774 DeletedPtrs.insert(BasePtr); 0
775 ----
776 return std::make_pair(NewBasePtr, PtrInc); 0
777 } ----
778 ----
779 Instruction *PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::rewriteForBucketElement( 0
780 std::pair Base, const BucketElement &Element, ----
781 Value *OffToBase, SmallPtrSet &DeletedPtrs) { ----
782 Instruction *NewBasePtr = Base.first; 0
783 Instruction *PtrInc = Base.second; 0
784 assert((NewBasePtr && PtrInc) && "base does not exist!\n"); 0
785 ----
786 Type *I8Ty = Type::getInt8Ty(PtrInc->getParent()->getContext()); 0
787 ----
788 Value *Ptr = getPointerOperandAndType(Element.Instr); 0
789 assert(Ptr && "No pointer operand"); 0
790 ----
791 Instruction *RealNewPtr; ----
792 if (!Element.Offset || 0
793 (isa(Element.Offset) && 0
794 cast(Element.Offset)->getValue()->isZero())) { 0
795 RealNewPtr = NewBasePtr; 0
796 } else { ----
797 Instruction *PtrIP = dyn_cast(Ptr); 0
798 if (PtrIP && isa(NewBasePtr) && 0
799 cast(NewBasePtr)->getParent() == PtrIP->getParent()) 0
800 PtrIP = nullptr; 0
801 else if (PtrIP && isa(PtrIP)) 0
802 PtrIP = &*PtrIP->getParent()->getFirstInsertionPt(); 0
803 else if (!PtrIP) 0
804 PtrIP = Element.Instr; 0
805 ----
806 assert(OffToBase && "There should be an offset for non base element!\n"); 0
807 GetElementPtrInst *NewPtr = GetElementPtrInst::Create( 0
808 I8Ty, PtrInc, OffToBase, ----
809 getInstrName(Element.Instr, GEPNodeOffNameSuffix), PtrIP); 0
810 if (!PtrIP) 0
811 NewPtr->insertAfter(cast(PtrInc)); 0
812 NewPtr->setIsInBounds(IsPtrInBounds(Ptr)); 0
813 RealNewPtr = NewPtr; 0
814 } ----
815 ----
816 Instruction *ReplNewPtr; ----
817 if (Ptr->getType() != RealNewPtr->getType()) { 0
818 ReplNewPtr = new BitCastInst(RealNewPtr, Ptr->getType(), 0
819 getInstrName(Ptr, CastNodeNameSuffix)); 0
820 ReplNewPtr->insertAfter(RealNewPtr); 0
821 } else ----
822 ReplNewPtr = RealNewPtr; 0
823 ----
824 Ptr->replaceAllUsesWith(ReplNewPtr); 0
825 DeletedPtrs.insert(Ptr); 0
826 ----
827 return ReplNewPtr; 0
828 } ----
829 ----
830 void PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::addOneCandidate( 0
831 Instruction *MemI, const SCEV *LSCEV, SmallVector &Buckets, ----
832 std::function isValidDiff, unsigned MaxCandidateNum) { ----
833 assert((MemI && getPointerOperandAndType(MemI)) && 0
834 "Candidate should be a memory instruction."); ----
835 assert(LSCEV && "Invalid SCEV for Ptr value."); 0
836 ----
837 bool FoundBucket = false; 0
838 for (auto &B : Buckets) { 0
839 if (cast(B.BaseSCEV)->getStepRecurrence(*SE) != 0
840 cast(LSCEV)->getStepRecurrence(*SE)) 0
841 continue; 0
842 const SCEV *Diff = SE->getMinusSCEV(LSCEV, B.BaseSCEV); 0
843 if (isValidDiff(Diff)) { 0
844 B.Elements.push_back(BucketElement(Diff, MemI)); 0
845 FoundBucket = true; 0
846 break; 0
847 } ----
848 } ----
849 ----
850 if (!FoundBucket) { 0
851 if (Buckets.size() == MaxCandidateNum) { 0
852 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can not prepare more chains, reach maximum limit " 0
853 << MaxCandidateNum << "\n"); ----
854 return; 0
855 } ----
856 Buckets.push_back(Bucket(LSCEV, MemI)); 0
857 } ----
858 } ----
859 ----
860 SmallVector PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::collectCandidates( 0
861 Loop *L, ----
862 std::function ----
863 isValidCandidate, ----
864 std::function isValidDiff, unsigned MaxCandidateNum) { ----
865 SmallVector Buckets; 0
866 ----
867 for (const auto &BB : L->blocks()) 0
868 for (auto &J : *BB) { 0
869 Value *PtrValue = nullptr; 0
870 Type *PointerElementType = nullptr; 0
871 PtrValue = getPointerOperandAndType(&J, &PointerElementType); 0
872 ----
873 if (!PtrValue) 0
874 continue; 0
875 ----
876 if (PtrValue->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace()) 0
877 continue; 0
878 ----
879 if (L->isLoopInvariant(PtrValue)) 0
880 continue; 0
881 ----
882 const SCEV *LSCEV = SE->getSCEVAtScope(PtrValue, L); 0
883 const SCEVAddRecExpr *LARSCEV = dyn_cast(LSCEV); 0
884 if (!LARSCEV || LARSCEV->getLoop() != L) 0
885 continue; 0
886 ----
887 // Mark that we have candidates for preparing. ----
888 HasCandidateForPrepare = true; 0
889 ----
890 if (isValidCandidate(&J, PtrValue, PointerElementType)) 0
891 addOneCandidate(&J, LSCEV, Buckets, isValidDiff, MaxCandidateNum); 0
892 } ----
893 return Buckets; 0
894 } ----
895 ----
896 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::prepareBaseForDispFormChain(Bucket &BucketChain, 0
897 PrepForm Form) { ----
898 // RemainderOffsetInfo details: ----
899 // key: value of (Offset urem DispConstraint). For DSForm, it can ----
900 // be [0, 4). ----
901 // first of pair: the index of first BucketElement whose remainder is equal ----
902 // to key. For key 0, this value must be 0. ----
903 // second of pair: number of load/stores with the same remainder. ----
904 DenseMap> RemainderOffsetInfo; 0
905 ----
906 for (unsigned j = 0, je = BucketChain.Elements.size(); j != je; ++j) { 0
907 if (!BucketChain.Elements[j].Offset) 0
908 RemainderOffsetInfo[0] = std::make_pair(0, 1); 0
909 else { ----
910 unsigned Remainder = cast(BucketChain.Elements[j].Offset) 0
911 ->getAPInt() 0
912 .urem(Form); 0
913 if (!RemainderOffsetInfo.contains(Remainder)) 0
914 RemainderOffsetInfo[Remainder] = std::make_pair(j, 1); 0
915 else ----
916 RemainderOffsetInfo[Remainder].second++; 0
917 } ----
918 } ----
919 // Currently we choose the most profitable base as the one which has the max ----
920 // number of load/store with same remainder. ----
921 // FIXME: adjust the base selection strategy according to load/store offset ----
922 // distribution. ----
923 // For example, if we have one candidate chain for DS form preparation, which ----
924 // contains following load/stores with different remainders: ----
925 // 1: 10 load/store whose remainder is 1; ----
926 // 2: 9 load/store whose remainder is 2; ----
927 // 3: 1 for remainder 3 and 0 for remainder 0; ----
928 // Now we will choose the first load/store whose remainder is 1 as base and ----
929 // adjust all other load/stores according to new base, so we will get 10 DS ----
930 // form and 10 X form. ----
931 // But we should be more clever, for this case we could use two bases, one for ----
932 // remainder 1 and the other for remainder 2, thus we could get 19 DS form and ----
933 // 1 X form. ----
934 unsigned MaxCountRemainder = 0; 0
935 for (unsigned j = 0; j < (unsigned)Form; j++) 0
936 if ((RemainderOffsetInfo.contains(j)) && 0
937 RemainderOffsetInfo[j].second > 0
938 RemainderOffsetInfo[MaxCountRemainder].second) 0
939 MaxCountRemainder = j; 0
940 ----
941 // Abort when there are too few insts with common base. ----
942 if (RemainderOffsetInfo[MaxCountRemainder].second < DispFormPrepMinThreshold) 0
943 return false; 0
944 ----
945 // If the first value is most profitable, no needed to adjust BucketChain ----
946 // elements as they are substracted the first value when collecting. ----
947 if (MaxCountRemainder == 0) 0
948 return true; 0
949 ----
950 // Adjust load/store to the new chosen base. ----
951 const SCEV *Offset = ----
952 BucketChain.Elements[RemainderOffsetInfo[MaxCountRemainder].first].Offset; 0
953 BucketChain.BaseSCEV = SE->getAddExpr(BucketChain.BaseSCEV, Offset); 0
954 for (auto &E : BucketChain.Elements) { 0
955 if (E.Offset) 0
956 E.Offset = cast(SE->getMinusSCEV(E.Offset, Offset)); 0
957 else ----
958 E.Offset = cast(SE->getNegativeSCEV(Offset)); 0
959 } ----
960 ----
961 std::swap(BucketChain.Elements[RemainderOffsetInfo[MaxCountRemainder].first], 0
962 BucketChain.Elements[0]); 0
963 return true; 0
964 } 0
965 ----
966 // FIXME: implement a more clever base choosing policy. ----
967 // Currently we always choose an exist load/store offset. This maybe lead to ----
968 // suboptimal code sequences. For example, for one DS chain with offsets ----
969 // {-32769, 2003, 2007, 2011}, we choose -32769 as base offset, and left disp ----
970 // for load/stores are {0, 34772, 34776, 34780}. Though each offset now is a ----
971 // multipler of 4, it cannot be represented by sint16. ----
972 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::prepareBaseForUpdateFormChain(Bucket &BucketChain) { 0
973 // We have a choice now of which instruction's memory operand we use as the ----
974 // base for the generated PHI. Always picking the first instruction in each ----
975 // bucket does not work well, specifically because that instruction might ----
976 // be a prefetch (and there are no pre-increment dcbt variants). Otherwise, ----
977 // the choice is somewhat arbitrary, because the backend will happily ----
978 // generate direct offsets from both the pre-incremented and ----
979 // post-incremented pointer values. Thus, we'll pick the first non-prefetch ----
980 // instruction in each bucket, and adjust the recurrence and other offsets ----
981 // accordingly. ----
982 for (int j = 0, je = BucketChain.Elements.size(); j != je; ++j) { 0
983 if (auto *II = dyn_cast(BucketChain.Elements[j].Instr)) 0
984 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::prefetch) 0
985 continue; 0
986 ----
987 // If we'd otherwise pick the first element anyway, there's nothing to do. ----
988 if (j == 0) 0
989 break; 0
990 ----
991 // If our chosen element has no offset from the base pointer, there's ----
992 // nothing to do. ----
993 if (!BucketChain.Elements[j].Offset || 0
994 cast(BucketChain.Elements[j].Offset)->isZero()) 0
995 break; 0
996 ----
997 const SCEV *Offset = BucketChain.Elements[j].Offset; 0
998 BucketChain.BaseSCEV = SE->getAddExpr(BucketChain.BaseSCEV, Offset); 0
999 for (auto &E : BucketChain.Elements) { 0
1000 if (E.Offset) 0
1001 E.Offset = cast(SE->getMinusSCEV(E.Offset, Offset)); 0
1002 else ----
1003 E.Offset = cast(SE->getNegativeSCEV(Offset)); 0
1004 } ----
1005 ----
1006 std::swap(BucketChain.Elements[j], BucketChain.Elements[0]); 0
1007 break; 0
1008 } ----
1009 return true; 0
1010 } ----
1011 ----
1012 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::rewriteLoadStores( 0
1013 Loop *L, Bucket &BucketChain, SmallSet &BBChanged, ----
1014 PrepForm Form) { ----
1015 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1016 ----
1017 const SCEVAddRecExpr *BasePtrSCEV = ----
1018 cast(BucketChain.BaseSCEV); 0
1019 if (!BasePtrSCEV->isAffine()) 0
1020 return MadeChange; 0
1021 ----
1022 BasicBlock *Header = L->getHeader(); 0
1023 SCEVExpander SCEVE(*SE, Header->getModule()->getDataLayout(), 0
1024 "loopprepare-formrewrite"); 0
1025 if (!SCEVE.isSafeToExpand(BasePtrSCEV->getStart())) 0
1026 return MadeChange; 0
1027 ----
1028 SmallPtrSet DeletedPtrs; 0
1029 ----
1030 // For some DS form load/store instructions, it can also be an update form, ----
1031 // if the stride is constant and is a multipler of 4. Use update form if ----
1032 // prefer it. ----
1033 bool CanPreInc = (Form == UpdateForm || 0
1034 ((Form == DSForm) && 0
1035 isa(BasePtrSCEV->getStepRecurrence(*SE)) && 0
1036 !cast(BasePtrSCEV->getStepRecurrence(*SE)) 0
1037 ->getAPInt() 0
1038 .urem(4) && 0
1039 PreferUpdateForm)); 0
1040 ----
1041 std::pair Base = ----
1042 rewriteForBase(L, BasePtrSCEV, BucketChain.Elements.begin()->Instr, 0
1043 CanPreInc, Form, SCEVE, DeletedPtrs); ----
1044 ----
1045 if (!Base.first || !Base.second) 0
1046 return MadeChange; 0
1047 ----
1048 // Keep track of the replacement pointer values we've inserted so that we ----
1049 // don't generate more pointer values than necessary. ----
1050 SmallPtrSet NewPtrs; 0
1051 NewPtrs.insert(Base.first); 0
1052 ----
1053 for (const BucketElement &BE : llvm::drop_begin(BucketChain.Elements)) { 0
1054 Value *Ptr = getPointerOperandAndType(BE.Instr); 0
1055 assert(Ptr && "No pointer operand"); 0
1056 if (NewPtrs.count(Ptr)) 0
1057 continue; 0
1058 ----
1059 Instruction *NewPtr = rewriteForBucketElement( 0
1060 Base, BE, ----
1061 BE.Offset ? cast(BE.Offset)->getValue() : nullptr, 0
1062 DeletedPtrs); ----
1063 assert(NewPtr && "wrong rewrite!\n"); 0
1064 NewPtrs.insert(NewPtr); 0
1065 } ----
1066 ----
1067 // Clear the rewriter cache, because values that are in the rewriter's cache ----
1068 // can be deleted below, causing the AssertingVH in the cache to trigger. ----
1069 SCEVE.clear(); 0
1070 ----
1071 for (auto *Ptr : DeletedPtrs) { 0
1072 if (Instruction *IDel = dyn_cast(Ptr)) 0
1073 BBChanged.insert(IDel->getParent()); 0
1074 RecursivelyDeleteTriviallyDeadInstructions(Ptr); 0
1075 } ----
1076 ----
1077 MadeChange = true; 0
1078 ----
1079 SuccPrepCount++; 0
1080 ----
1081 if (Form == DSForm && !CanPreInc) 0
1082 DSFormChainRewritten++; 0
1083 else if (Form == DQForm) 0
1084 DQFormChainRewritten++; 0
1085 else if (Form == UpdateForm || (Form == DSForm && CanPreInc)) 0
1086 UpdFormChainRewritten++; 0
1087 ----
1088 return MadeChange; 0
1089 } 0
1090 ----
1091 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::updateFormPrep(Loop *L, 0
1092 SmallVector &Buckets) { ----
1093 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1094 if (Buckets.empty()) 0
1095 return MadeChange; 0
1096 SmallSet BBChanged; 0
1097 for (auto &Bucket : Buckets) 0
1098 // The base address of each bucket is transformed into a phi and the others ----
1099 // are rewritten based on new base. ----
1100 if (prepareBaseForUpdateFormChain(Bucket)) 0
1101 MadeChange |= rewriteLoadStores(L, Bucket, BBChanged, UpdateForm); 0
1102 ----
1103 if (MadeChange) 0
1104 for (auto *BB : BBChanged) 0
1105 DeleteDeadPHIs(BB); 0
1106 return MadeChange; 0
1107 } 0
1108 ----
1109 bool PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::dispFormPrep(Loop *L, 0
1110 SmallVector &Buckets, ----
1111 PrepForm Form) { ----
1112 bool MadeChange = false; 0
1113 ----
1114 if (Buckets.empty()) 0
1115 return MadeChange; 0
1116 ----
1117 SmallSet BBChanged; 0
1118 for (auto &Bucket : Buckets) { 0
1119 if (Bucket.Elements.size() < DispFormPrepMinThreshold) 0
1120 continue; 0
1121 if (prepareBaseForDispFormChain(Bucket, Form)) 0
1122 MadeChange |= rewriteLoadStores(L, Bucket, BBChanged, Form); 0
1123 } ----
1124 ----
1125 if (MadeChange) 0
1126 for (auto *BB : BBChanged) 0
1127 DeleteDeadPHIs(BB); 0
1128 return MadeChange; 0
1129 } 0
1130 ----
1131 // Find the loop invariant increment node for SCEV BasePtrIncSCEV. ----
1132 // bb.loop.preheader: ----
1133 // %start = ... ----
1134 // bb.loop.body: ----
1135 // %phinode = phi [ %start, %bb.loop.preheader ], [ %add, %bb.loop.body ] ----
1136 // ... ----
1137 // %add = add %phinode, %inc ; %inc is what we want to get. ----
1138 // ----
1139 Value *PPCLoopInstrFormPrep::getNodeForInc(Loop *L, Instruction *MemI, 0
1140 const SCEV *BasePtrIncSCEV) { ----
1141 // If the increment is a constant, no definition is needed. ----
1142 // Return the value directly. ----
1143 if (isa(BasePtrIncSCEV)) 0
1144 return cast(BasePtrIncSCEV)->getValue(); 0
1145 ----
1146 if (!SE->isLoopInvariant(BasePtrIncSCEV, L)) 0
1147 return nullptr; 0
1148 ----
1149 BasicBlock *BB = MemI->getParent(); 0
1150 if (!BB) 0
1151 return nullptr; 0
1152 ----
1153 BasicBlock *LatchBB = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
1154 ----
1155 if (!LatchBB) 0
1156 return nullptr; 0
1157 ----
1158 // Run through the PHIs and check their operands to find valid representation ----
1159 // for the increment SCEV. ----
1160 iterator_range PHIIter = BB->phis(); 0
1161 for (auto &CurrentPHI : PHIIter) { 0
1162 PHINode *CurrentPHINode = dyn_cast(&CurrentPHI); 0
1163 if (!CurrentPHINode) 0
1164 continue; 0
1165 ----
1166 if (!SE->isSCEVable(CurrentPHINode->getType())) 0
1167 continue; 0
1168 ----
1169 const SCEV *PHISCEV = SE->getSCEVAtScope(CurrentPHINode, L); 0
1170 ----
1171 const SCEVAddRecExpr *PHIBasePtrSCEV = dyn_cast(PHISCEV); 0
1172 if (!PHIBasePtrSCEV) 0
1173 continue; 0
1174 ----
1175 const SCEV *PHIBasePtrIncSCEV = PHIBasePtrSCEV->getStepRecurrence(*SE); 0
1176 ----
1177 if (!PHIBasePtrIncSCEV || (PHIBasePtrIncSCEV != BasePtrIncSCEV)) 0
1178 continue; 0
1179 ----
1180 // Get the incoming value from the loop latch and check if the value has ----
1181 // the add form with the required increment. ----
1182 if (CurrentPHINode->getBasicBlockIndex(LatchBB) < 0) 0
1183 continue; 0
1184 if (Instruction *I = dyn_cast( 0
1185 CurrentPHINode->getIncomingValueForBlock(LatchBB))) { ----
1186 Value *StrippedBaseI = I; 0
1187 while (BitCastInst *BC = dyn_cast(StrippedBaseI)) 0
